column15: Involve with fundamental and critical aspects of learner , about manner of living

column18: Are these problems being solved by the School?
column19: Any other factors , according to you , which contribute to happiness index
Focusing on learnings gained by the students instead of the marks obtained.
Instead of just focusing on the learning part, schools should also focus on implementing them.  And of course not implementing them in assignments but something real life applications.
less homework, less exam pressure, lesser importance of marks. More emphasis on practical learning and extracurricular activities like, debates, MUN's, tech contests, science contests.

A more creative form of assessment and testing to be conducted instead of the traditional manners, in such a way as to focus on overall development of the students, along with better understanding of the concepts.
Picnic, trip and learning according to their age and level without any pressure.
All students should be treated equally . Average students should be given more importance.  They should be given more importance to participate in all activities.
Teachers should live with students friendly and sportingly so that they can be more interested in studying
